    <title>SAP for Utilities - why go? #SAP4U</title>
    <updated>2023-09-29T10:15:49+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>TammyPowlas</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/82</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;A href="https://www.sap.com/events/2023-10-09-us-pe-asug.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;SAP for Utilities&lt;/A&gt;, October 9-11, Chicago - why go?&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;P style="overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 0px"&gt;&lt;IMG class="migrated-image" src="https://community.sap.com/legacyfs/online/storage/blog_attachments/2023/09/sap4u.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;P class="image_caption" style="text-align: center;font-style: italic"&gt;Source: ASUG&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
In a few short days, SAP for Utilties, presented by ASUG, will begin.&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
So why attend?&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
Here are some reasons:&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
1. &lt;STRONG&gt;Learn about SAP's vision for the future&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
SAP has a keynote "Keynote-The Future of Energy: Innovations in Utilities, Generation, and Storage"&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
2. &lt;STRONG&gt;Hear from fellow utility customers&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
I have a big list of customers presenting below.&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
3. &lt;STRONG&gt;Participate in lunch table topics&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
On Tuesday, we're having a "Lunch and Learn Topic Table on SAP S/4HANA: Implementation"&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;Join this discussion if you are mid-project or have already gone live with SAP S/4HANA. You will learn from peers who are already on the journey and have made mission-critical decisions. You’ll gain knowledge on lessons learned to ensure success in your future endeavors&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
More here:&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;P style="overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 0px"&gt;&lt;IMG class="migrated-image" src="https://community.sap.com/legacyfs/online/storage/blog_attachments/2023/09/lunchtopics.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;P class="image_caption" style="text-align: center;font-style: italic"&gt;Source: ASUG&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
4. &lt;STRONG&gt;Explore solutions for utilities&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
Visit partners and SAP booths to share and exchange ideas&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
5. &lt;STRONG&gt;Network with your peers&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
October 9th starts with a "Beers with Peers" session.&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;STRONG&gt;Gain insights from customer stories:&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;UL&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Evaluating the Use of RISE with SAP During &lt;STRONG&gt;Lincoln Electric System&lt;/STRONG&gt; Digital Transformation&lt;BR /&gt;
"Lincoln Electric System is preparing to move to SAP S/4HANA and is working with SAP to determine the appropriate functional and technical scope. "&lt;BR /&gt;
Patrick Gans is active in the community, and will be interesting to learn more about their plans&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Getting Everything You Need from SAP Service Cloud with &lt;STRONG&gt;Southern California Edison&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;P style="padding-left: 40px"&gt;SoCal Edison is always at the forefront and this time it is no different - listen to their experience with SAP Service Cloud&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;UL&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Case Study:&lt;STRONG&gt; Hawaiian Electric Company&lt;/STRONG&gt; Partners with Rizing to Modernize Mobile Work &amp;amp; Field Service. "Hawaiian Electric Company (HECO) has embarked on a transformative journey to better leverage its existing SAP implementation and modernize its software and business processes"&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Central Hudson’s&lt;/STRONG&gt; Journey to SAP S/4HANA Real-Time Reporting on SAP Analytics Cloud (SAC)&lt;BR /&gt;
Everyone wants real time reporting with S/4HANA and this time Central Hudson also talks about using it with SAC&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Optimizing SAP S/4HANA for Digital Transformation and Growth at &lt;STRONG&gt;Summit Utilities&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
"Summit Utilities recently completed a Digital Transformation, enabling an end-to-end process coverage across ERP. They also deployed the full solution in just one year, leveraging a cloud-first strategy and replatforming 34 interfacing systems"&lt;BR /&gt;
34 systems...wow&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;SAP Security: Before, During, and After a RISE with SAP Migration with &lt;STRONG&gt;Snohomish PUD&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
At last year's event, many executives said cybersecurity was a top priority for their utility. I am glad that our great SAP Community Utilties superstar &lt;SPAN class="mention-scrubbed"&gt;marc.rosson2&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;is covering this.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;AMI 2.0 &amp;amp; SAP integration using BTP&lt;BR /&gt;
Marc is back covering this important topic.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Doubling Down on US EPA's Lead and Copper Rule Inventory with SAP&lt;BR /&gt;
Very important topic for US water utilities with &lt;STRONG&gt;Metropolitan District&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Process-Centric Transformation: A Data-Driven Approach to Future Innovation with &lt;STRONG&gt;Southern California Edison&lt;/STRONG&gt; -SoCal Edison discusses using Signavio&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Inclusive Payments: Leaving No Customer Behind in 2023&lt;BR /&gt;
A session with the great &lt;STRONG&gt;Metropolitan Utilities District&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Customer Core: Delivering Easy Fast Experiences&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;STRONG&gt;Dominion&lt;/STRONG&gt;, my electric utility, discusses the following their Customer Core project that implemented the following three primary applications:&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;UL&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;SAP, including SAP S/4HANA for Utilities and SAP C/4HANA&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Siemens’ Meter Data Management (MDM) system EnergyIP&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;SEW’s customer self-service system (Self Service Accelerator—SSA)&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;The &lt;STRONG&gt;Oklahoma City Water Utilities&lt;/STRONG&gt; Trust (OCWUT) RISE with SAP Journey&lt;BR /&gt;
They share their RISE journey&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Customer Panel Discussion: Implementing Utility Dispatch with SAP &amp;amp; Idea Jam&lt;BR /&gt;
Several utilities are on this panel, including &lt;STRONG&gt;Loudoun Water, TECO Energy, and Liberty Utilities&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Enabling a Next-Generation Customer Service Experience with &lt;STRONG&gt;New Jersey Resources&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
This will be interesting to know which cloud products they used.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Leveraging SAP BTP to Future Proof Development&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;STRONG&gt;Oklahoma Gas &amp;amp; Electric&lt;/STRONG&gt; covers their use of BTP&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;Navigating Change Lessons Learned from a Major SAP S/4HANA Project with &lt;STRONG&gt;NW Natural&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
NW Natural shares their S/4HANA journey&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
 	&lt;LI&gt;“Crawl, Walk, Run” How &lt;STRONG&gt;Liberty Utilities&lt;/STRONG&gt; Achieves Operational Excellence with SAP Service &amp;amp; Asset&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
The great ASUG Conference Producer Alyssa Perna shared some highlights:&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;P style="overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 0px"&gt;&lt;IMG class="migrated-image" src="https://community.sap.com/legacyfs/online/storage/blog_attachments/2023/09/agenda-highlights.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;P class="image_caption" style="text-align: center;font-style: italic"&gt;Source: ASUG&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
See you &lt;A href="https://www.asug.com/events/sap-for-utilities-presented-by-asug" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;there&lt;/A&gt;?&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
Since I am posting this on a Friday, here's a video of this same event I attended 9 years ago:&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;BR /&gt;
&lt;IFRAME width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/YqMIkt415T4?si=TpdmueFJuVN_nAUz" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""&gt;&lt;/IFRAME&gt;</content>
